# 2. 大晦日のすごしかた

Mizuki: <K, I tweaked that thing from earlier. What do you think of this version?>
Kanade: <This is much better... Let's go with it.>
Mizuki: <Yay! I'm glad I asked you for feedback.>
Ena: <Then why don't we call it a night? We've been working for so long...>
Mafuyu: <Okay. I'm going to log off.>
Kanade: <Alright. I'm staying up a bit longer to work, so you can ping me if you need anything.>
Mizuki: <Oh! Guys, before you go...>
Kanade: <What is it?>
Mizuki: <Are you all busy tomorrow? Because if not, I thought we could meet up and...>
Ena: <No thanks.>
Mizuki: <Whaaat? Why, Ena?!>
Ena: <Because it's cold. I don't want to leave my cozy house.>
Kanade: <Same here... My body just stops moving when it's cold.>
Mizuki: <Aww, seriously...?! What about you, Yuki?>
Mafuyu: <Cram school for the holidays. I may even be late logging in here.>
Mizuki: <Yikes, that's pretty rough to have classes while everyone else is on vacation...>
Ena: <If you have nothing to do, Mizuki, why don't you just stay at home?>
Kanade: <Didn't you say you're going to a gig or a show for New Year's Eve...?>
Mizuki: <Oh, the anime song countdown event? Unfortunately, I couldn't get tickets...>
Mizuki: <It wasn't that popular last year but they got some famous singers lined up this year, so tickets sold out fast.>
Mizuki: <I got tickets the last two years, so I thought I was good to go but...>
Ena: <Then just stay home like I said. Don't get desperate and try to organize something on the fly.>
Mizuki: <I know but... My parents left for the holidays to visit my sis living overseas...>
Mizuki: <So I have to cook my own dinner and stuff. It's too much of a bother, so I want to go out to eat.>
Mizuki: <Which is why I thought it'd be nice to go out with you guys...>
Ena: <Pity that's not going to happen...>
Mizuki: <Are you seriously going to refuse my invite? Don't you want to go hang out together?!>
Ena: <Nope.>
Kanade: <Sorry, Mizuki...>
Mizuki: <Well, I tried...>
Mafuyu: <I'm logging off now. See you later tonight.>
Mizuki: <Laters...>
Mizuki: (Well, I failed to get anyone. Is there really no one who can hang out with me tomorrow?)
Mizuki: (I guess everybody's already got plans. But N25 seemed like my best bet...)
Mizuki: Sigh...
Young Girl A: So, did you decide what you're gonna get?
Young Girl B: Oh, this cake looks sooo cute. I'm getting this one!
Mizuki: (Sigh... Look at all the happy people having a good time here...)
Mizuki: (Man, if only I managed to get a ticket for that show, I'd be having a good time today too...)
Young Girl A: Hey, so what are you doing tonight?
Young Girl B: I'm going to a New Year's Eve party with friends, and staying over at a friend's house.
Young Girl A: Aww, that sounds nice! You're gonna have a blast!
Mizuki: (A New Year's Eve party, huh. I wish I was going to one...)
Mizuki: (As much as I'd like to party with N25, Mafuyu's parents seem super strict, while Ena and Kanade don't want to go out at all...)
Mizuki: (Hold on a minute. There's a solution to that...!)
Mizuki: <Guys! Listen up! I've got this amazing idea!>
Ena: <Ugh, not another one. And can you stop shouting into your mic?>
Mizuki: <Hahaha. Sorry.>
Mafuyu: <Oh, you're all here already...?>
Kanade: <I thought you were going to be late today because of cram school, Yuki?>
Mafuyu: <I was but classes ended early.>
Mizuki: <Perfect timing! I was just about to reveal my super exciting idea!>
Kanade: <Idea...?>
Mizuki: <Yup! Let's have a New Year's Eve Countdown Party!>
